Postoperative Care for hip Replacement.
1. Get in and out of bed and walk short distances (typically 150 to 300 feet) with the aid of assistive devices, such as a walker or crutches.
2. Eat meals sitting up.
3. Perform simple exercises.
4. Follow precautions to avoid dislocating the new hip.
5. go up and down stairs (using a handrail and assistive devices).